{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"ANC1 visits experienced minor disruptions in Dec 2023 (~7,400 visits below expected), followed by disruptions in March 2024 (~7,800 visits below expected) and June 2024 (~7,000 below expected). Following these disruptions, ANC1 showed strong recovery with surpluses during April 2024 (~7,800 visits above expected), and a more sustained period of  surplus in 2025 with July 2025 (~6,500 above expected), September 2025 (~11,000 above expected), and December 2025 (~7,850 above expected).

ANC4 visits consistently stayed at or very close to expected levels throughout the period, with actual values matching expected values in nearly all months. This suggests stable, predictable utilization patterns for fourth antenatal care visits.
"},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"dda09303-e364-48a6-86a7-f7de325b6369","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"ANC1 shows some volatility, while ANC4 stays near trend, but continuity gap remains"}}

