{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"ANC1 volumes showed variability with distinct low points in late 2023 (~60,500 in Dec 2023) and mid-2024 (~59,500 in June 2024). Notable peaks occurred in early 2024 (~78,900 in April), mid-2024 (~76,600 in Jan), and late 2025 (~81,600 in Sept).

ANC4 showed gradual growth from ~38,000 visits in July 2023 to 44,500 visits in Dec 2025 — representing a 16% increase.

The gap of ~27,000-30,000 visits between ANC1 and ANC4 indicates significant attrition in the antenatal care continuum, with only about 60% of women completing their fourth visit. ","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"62817f72-fce6-46c0-80c0-10ac3f9670f7","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in antenatal care","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}
